Zwelinzima Vavi, General Secretary of the South African Federation of Trade Unions. AFP/John Wessels JOHANNESBURG - Mining bosses should not be paying themselves millions while refusing to improve the wages of ordinary workers. That is the assertion of Saftu General Secretary, Zwelinzima Vavi. READ: Sibanye-Stillwater employees camp outside Union Buildings He says mining companies are exploiting black workers. Vavi says the cost of living in South Africa is soaring and workers have the right to be given a fair increase in order to afford the basics. Click here to watch the full interview.